  "explanation": "A post-order approach (Right, Left, Root) can flatten the tree in place. Keep track of the previously visited node in this traversal. For each node, set its right to the previous node, its left to null, and then update the previous node to be the current node.",
  "answer": "def flatten(root):\n    prev = [None]\n    def traverse(node):\n        if not node: return\n        traverse(node.right)\n        traverse(node.left)\n        node.right = prev[0]\n        node.left = None\n        prev[0] = node\n    traverse(root)\n    return root",
